<h1>Mind-Boggling Facts About Gender Inequality</h1>

<center><img src="https://s-media-cache-ak0.pinimg.com/236x/02/01/59/0201590feecc56a11e2b26424b1a9a78.jpg"</center>

<p>1. Women make up 46% of the total U.S. labor force. </p>

<p>2. Women make only 77.5 cents for every dollar that men earn.</p>

<p>3. Women in professional specialty occupations were found to earn just 72.7% of what men in the same position earned.</p>

<p>4. Women may work longer to receive the promotions that provide access to higher pay.</p>

<p>5. Women business owners employ 35% more people than all the Fortune 500 companies combined.</p>

<h2>"10 Surprising Statistics on Women in the Workplace." CollegeTimes. 2010. Web. 25 July 2016."</h2>
